    '{"type":"multiple_choice","choices":{"A":"Isoguanine and purine were detected in both meteorite samples but not in the soil sample.","B":"Adenine and xanthine were detected in both of the meteorite samples and in the soil sample.","C":"Hypoxanthine and purine were detected in both the Murchison meteorite sample 2 and in the soil sample.","D":"Isoguanine and hypoxanthine were detected in the Murchison meteorite sample 1 but not in sample 2."}}',
    'Choice A is the best answer. The researchers concluded that the meteorite’s nucleobases weren’t the result of soil
contamination. Presence of nucleobases in the meteorite and not in soil provides evidence that those nucleobases likely
didn’t come from the soil.
Choice B is incorrect. This choice doesn’t justify the conclusion. The researchers concluded that the meteorite’s nucleobases
