    'Choice A is the best answer. This choice provides evidence that directly links the presence of R. solanacearum-inhibiting
microbes in the soil to the health of tomato plants.
Choice B is incorrect. This choice would weaken the team’s conclusion. It suggests that the presence of the disease-causing
bacteria had no effect on the health of the tomato plants. Choice C is incorrect. This choice doesn’t support the team’s
conclusion. The conclusion is about microbes, not soil moisture. Choice D is incorrect. This choice would weaken the team’s
conclusion. It suggests that the presence of the bacteria-inhibiting microbe in soil had no effect on the health of the tomato
plants.',
