analysis, the researchers found that Acasta rocks dating to about 4.02 billion years ago (bya) most strongly resemble
modern rocks formed in a plume setting (an area in which hot rocks from Earth’s mantle flow upward into the crust). By
contrast, they found that Acasta rocks dating to about 3.75 bya and 3.6 bya have an isotope composition that is similar to
that of modern rocks formed in a subduction setting. Aarons’s team therefore concluded that ______
