    '{"type":"multiple_choice","choices":{"A":"diminishing the monetary reward that corporations might derive from their agreements with Indigenous communities.","B":"limiting the research that corporations conduct on the resources of the Indigenous communities with which they have","C":"preventing independent observers from determining whether the agreements guarantee equitable compensation for","D":"discouraging Indigenous communities from learning new methods for harvesting plants and animals from their"}}',
    'Choice C is the best answer because it most logically completes the argument about an unintended effect of the Nagoya
