    'Choice D is the best answer. Enrollment and attendance are logical ways to measure whether students are interested and
engaged. High enrollment and attendance suggests a high level of interest and engagement.
Choice A is incorrect. This choice doesn’t support the claim. Students’ preferences between hip-hop and rap aren’t relevant
