    'Choice C is the best answer because it most effectively uses data from the table to complete the comparison between
Pueblo tribal nations. The student identifies that the total area of Taos Pueblo is 156.2 square miles and needs to complete
the comparison with the total area of Nambé Pueblo. According to the table, Nambé Pueblo has a total area of 32.4 square
miles.
Choice A is incorrect because according to the table, 47.3 square miles is the area of Pueblo de San Ildefonso, not of Nambé
